.TH VOLBAR 1 "2024" "Volbar 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
volbar \- simple volume bar for X11 desktops
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B volbar
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Volbar is a simple, lightweight volume bar popup for X11 desktops. It displays volume changes with customizable themes, sizes, positions, and slider styles.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-size " \fISIZE\fR"
Window size: small, medium, or large (default: medium)
.TP
.BR \-\-placement " \fIPOS\fR"
Position: center, top, bottom, left, right, top-left, top-right, bottom-left, bottom-right (default: center)
.TP
.BR \-\-icon " on|off"
Show volume icon (default: on)
.TP
.BR \-\-percent " on|off"
Show percentage (default: on)
.TP
.BR \-\-slider " \fITYPE\fR"
Slider style: blocks, bar, dots, line, equals, hash, pipe, star, circle, diamond, triangle, arrow, square, bracket, paren, bar-simple (default: blocks)
.TP
.BR \-\-theme " \fINAME\fR"
Theme name from ~/.themes/volbar/ (default: default)
.TP
.BR \-\-corner\-radius " \fINUM\fR"
Corner radius in pixels (default: 8)
.TP
.BR \-\-timeout " \fIMS\fR"
Display timeout in milliseconds (default: 2000)
.TP
.BR \-\-start\-daemon
Start background monitoring daemon
.TP
.BR \-\-stop\-daemon
Stop running daemon
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-themes
List available themes
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-sliders
List available slider styles
.TP
.BR \-\-test\-themes
Preview all themes with current volume
.TP
.BR \-\-show
Show volume once and exit (default mode)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show volume bar:
.B volbar \-\-show
.TP
Show with custom theme and placement:
.B volbar \-\-show \-\-placement top-right \-\-theme cyberpunk
.TP
Show with custom slider style:
.B volbar \-\-show \-\-slider line
.TP
Start daemon mode:
.B volbar \-\-start\-daemon \-\-placement top-right
.TP
List available sliders:
.B volbar \-\-list\-sliders
.TP
Stop daemon:
.B volbar \-\-stop\-daemon
.SH THEMES
Themes are stored in
.IR ~/.themes/volbar/ .
The default theme is automatically created on first run.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.themes/volbar/
User theme directory
.TP
.I ~/.cache/volbar.pid
Daemon PID file
.SH AUDIO BACKENDS
Volbar auto-detects audio backends in this order:
.IP 1. 3
PipeWire (wpctl)
.IP 2. 3
PulseAudio (pactl)
.IP 3. 3
ALSA (amixer)
